The paper proposes a new method for modeling graph data using a hierarchical variational framework and a Bernoulli-Poisson link decoder. The method is evaluated on a variety of graph analytic tasks and outperforms state-of-the-art methods. Given these characteristics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The method also involves modeling implicit posteriors and rich dependency structures, which could potentially fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
